  "prompt": "What are some examples of player coming out of retirement after a long time?",
  "response": "There have been several notable instances of athletes coming out of retirement after an extended period. Here are a few examples:\n\n1. **Michael Jordan**: One of the most famous cases, Jordan retired from the NBA in 1993, returned in 1995 to play for the Chicago Bulls, retired again in 1999, and then came back to play for the Washington Wizards from 2001 to 2003.\n\n2. **George Foreman**: The former heavyweight boxing champion retired in 1977 but made a comeback in 1987. He gained prominence again by winning the heavyweight title in 1994 at the age of 45, making him the oldest heavyweight champion in history.\n\n3. **Brett Favre**: The NFL quarterback retired multiple times. He first retired in 2008 from the Green Bay Packers, then returned to play for the New York Jets, retired again, and came back with the Minnesota Vikings for two seasons before retiring for good in 2010.\n\n4. **Martina Hingis**: The Swiss tennis star retired for the first time in 2003 due to injuries, returned to the sport in 2006 for a brief period, retired again in 2007, and made a successful comeback in doubles in 2013, winning multiple Grand Slam titles before retiring permanently in 2017.\n\n5. **Randall Cunningham**: The NFL quarterback retired in 1996, but he returned in 1997 to play for the Minnesota Vikings and later played for the Dallas Cowboys and Baltimore Ravens before retiring again in 2002.\n\n6. **Kim Clijsters**: The Belgian tennis player first retired in 2007, returned in 2009, won three more Grand Slam singles titles, and retired again in 2012. She made another comeback in 2020 before retiring for the third time in 2022.\n\nThese athletes demonstrated remarkable skill and perseverance by returning to their respective sports after retirement, often achieving significant success.",
